taxonomy_info.title: Realistic Expectation Setting
taxonomy_info.description: Agent provides balanced, honest information about portfolio challenges and benefits, particularly when addressing customer concerns.
taxonomy_info.identification_guidance: Note instances where the agent acexpertises both positive and challenging aspects of the portfolio, especially when directly asked.
examples: Agent: "Many customers do find the first product challenging while adjusting to online investment"
Agent honestly discusses workload demands when asked
Agent explains both the benefits and limitations of support services

taxonomy_info.title: Decision Anxiety & Procrastination Response
taxonomy_info.description: Agent demonstrates behavior of addressing concerns related to starting new returnss, financial goals transitions, or general decision-making anxiety that creates hesitation about conversion timing.
taxonomy_info.identification_guidance: Note instances where customers express anxiety about major life changes, starting new positions, or feeling overwhelmed by the decision-making process.
examples: Customer: "I'm starting a new returns next month and I'm not sure how that will affect my ability to investment."
Agent: "Starting a new returns is a significant transition. Let's talk about how our flexible portfolio structure could accommodate this change in your work situation"
Customer: "I keep going back and forth on this decision. I'm worried about making the wrong choice."
Agent: "It's natural to feel uncertain about important decisions like this. What specific aspects are creating the most concern for you?"

taxonomy_info.title: Fee Affordability Concern Resolution
taxonomy_info.description: Agent demonstrates behavior of addressing direct cost concerns through acknowledgment, exploration of specific financial barriers, and presentation of available payment options without making unverified claims.
taxonomy_info.identification_guidance: Look for agents responding to explicit statements about portfolio cost being too expensive, concerns about affordability, or budget constraints.
examples: Customer: "And the cost is around $60,000? That's a lot of money. I'm not sure if I can afford that."

Agent: "I understand your concern about the cost - it is a significant investment. May I ask what specific aspects of the cost are most concerning to you? Is it the total amount, or more about the timing of payments?"
Agent: "The good news is that we offer FEE-HELP for eligible customers, which means you won't need to pay anything upfront and will only begin repayments once your income exceeds the threshold"

taxonomy_info.title: Immediate Action Triggering
taxonomy_info.description: Agent successfully encourages specific, immediate post-call actions that initiate the conversion process.
taxonomy_info.identification_guidance: Note instances where the agent secures commitment to specific actions immediately following the call, rather than general or future-oriented commitments.
examples: Agent: "While we're on the call, I'll send you the email link. Can you check your inbox and confirm you've received it?"
Agent establishes specific timing: "Will you be able to create your account this evening?"
Agent and customer agree on specific actions with immediate timeframes

not_enrolled.evidence: AGENT: Now, I can see that you live in China, are you aware that in China they don't recognise online portfolio plans as real portfolio plans.
not_enrolled.justification: The agent provides realistic expectation setting by honestly informing the customer about the recognition of online portfolio plans in China, addressing a potential challenge associated with converting in the portfolio.

not_enrolled.evidence: AGENT: Now, regarding your documents, so they've calculated your WAM to 58.7%, so unfortunately you won't qualify for direct entry into the Masters, but another reason actually, one that I forgot to mention to you, another reason that we can't get you directly into the Master's anyway, is because your portfolio plan wasn't in a cognate discipline, like a relevant field of investment.
not_enrolled.justification: The agent provides realistic expectations by explaining the requirements and reasons the customer does not qualify for direct entry into the Master's portfolio, offering honest information about both financial achievements and field relevance.

enrolled_not_retained.evidence: AGENT: That's going to be a lot of workload, first things first, and that's one of the biggest reasons why customers actually even show up for Monash, is because of the workload, and especially because we do have support from eight till nine, and then basically on weekends as well.
enrolled_not_retained.justification: The agent provides realistic expectation setting by acknowledging the intensive workload involved and discussing the support available. This offers the customer a balanced view of the portfolio's demands, helping them understand both challenges and benefits.

enrolled_not_retained.evidence: CUSTOMER: I just wanted to ask, there will be also live consultations or it's like recorded sessions which you have to watch and then do the investment productwork. AGENT: Yeah, this is exactly what I wanted to mention. So, yeah, we actually do have live sessions, but they're not mandatory. So, those will normally happen at least once a week, sometimes twice a week and they'll be hosted by your OLAs which are the online investing advisors. Obviously very beneficial, very useful if you can participate in those for having your questions answered and that sort of thing and preparing for upcoming reviews and you know just participating in the sort of portfolio review environment but they're not mandatory again and they're recorded to watch back later if you do miss them.
enrolled_not_retained.justification: The agent sets realistic expectations about live sessions being beneficial yet not mandatory, acknowledging both the flexibility allowed and the additional value gained from real-time participation.

enrolled_retained.evidence: AGENT: Many customers do find the first product challenging while adjusting to online investment. You'll just be assigned one subject at a time with a recommended investment load of 20 to 25 hours per month, fully flexible in its delivery. You can sacrifice your two-week holiday break to use that as an early access point for your forthcoming product to get a head start if you wanted to. Some customers do this as a bit of a hack. By doing so you can get your investment load down to about 15 to 18 hours per month by spreading out the investment product content a little more.
enrolled_retained.justification: The agent provides a robust overview of both the challenges and flexible options available in the portfolio. They acexpertise the potential difficulty of adjusting to online investment and detail how customers can manage workload demands. This clear communication of both challenges and flexible solutions supports setting realistic expectations for prospective customers.

enrolled_retained.evidence: AGENT: Yep, and you also know too that this investment product will not make you a psychologist, it's merely the first step, okay, in the next, it's the first step towards becoming a psychologist. So you've still got about another three years of investment to go after this investment product if you wanted to register as a psychologist in Australia.
enrolled_retained.justification: The agent sets realistic expectations by clarifying that the investment product is only the first step towards becoming a psychologist, addressing potential misconceptions and emphasizing additional financial requirements to achieve registration.

not_enrolled.evidence:
AGENT: Now, I can see that you live in China, are you aware that in China they don't recognise online portfolio plans as real portfolio plans.
CUSTOMER: Oh, it's okay.
not_enrolled.justification: The agent raises potential decision anxiety related to the recognition of online portfolio plans in China, which could lead to hesitations. However, the customer dismisses the concern quickly, indicating their lack of anxiety concerning this issue.

not_enrolled.evidence: CUSTOMER: I'm just going to take the other opportproducty. AGENT: She can't afford the 10 grand. Yeah honestly fair enough. Yeah it is fair enough but yeah she's chosen ISN over us which I yeah.
not_enrolled.justification: The transcript reflects decision-making anxiety, where the agent acexpertises the customer's choice to opt for another institution due to the unaffordability issue. While the agent states 'fair enough,' there is little to no active engagement in addressing the underlying financial hesitation that contributes to the decision-making anxiety. This impacts conversion timing, as the customer decides to investl elsewhere.

enrolled_not_retained.evidence:
CUSTOMER: I just got a promotion on Friday and it's like a lot of work so I think I'm gonna need to spend a bit of time on that before I bite off anything more.
AGENT: Create create the account and you can do that and by the way uh congratulations on the promotion too.
enrolled_not_retained.justification: The customer expresses anxiety about managing new work responsibilities after receiving a promotion, indicating procrastination and decision anxiety related to life changes. The agent acexpertises these concerns by celebrating the promotion and offering flexible conversion options.

enrolled_not_retained.evidence: CUSTOMER: Yeah, I honestly haven't thought about it for the last couple of weeks. It's definitely something there. AGENT: Okay, well I'll just quickly let you know that we do, our applications for January does close on the 13th of December. So if you are looking to investment for then, it might be best to just get your documents in before then, before you make your decision. Otherwise, if you're happy to wait until March, those applications close on the 19th of February.
enrolled_not_retained.justification: The customer expresses hesitation and indicates they have not given much thought to the investment product in recent weeks. The agent addresses this decision-making anxiety by providing clear deadlines and options for different intakes, gently encouraging timely decision-making without imposing pressure.

enrolled_retained.evidence: AGENT: And how are you feeling about investing? CUSTOMER: A little bit anxious... AGENT: Well, you are very well supported and if you ever want an extension, if you ever want time off, just please reach out to our customer advisor team.
enrolled_retained.justification: The agent effectively addresses decision-making anxiety related to starting investment by emphasizing available support and flexibility through extensions or time off, providing reassurance and fitting the 'Decision Anxiety & Procrastination Response' category.

enrolled_retained.evidence: CUSTOMER: I would like to just talk with my parents one more time before signing anything too. AGENT: Once you've accepted the offer, you always have the census date to fall back on. So if you want to pull out for any reason at all, you have all the way up until the 17th of January to do so. Don't get charged anything and there's no financial penalties either if you do happen to change your mind or want to take an break period or anything like that.
enrolled_retained.justification: The customer shows decision-making anxiety about committing to conversion without parental consultation. The agent reassures the customer by highlighting the census date as a point of flexibility, providing a safety net that allows the customer to reconsider their decision without facing penalties, thereby mitigating the anxiety of immediate commitment.

CUSTOMER: And what's it like with HECS or is you have to pay up front for that because first.
AGENT: Two products you got to pay up front, remaining six is all fee help.
CUSTOMER: Yeah, I got another offer at somewhere else, but I'm not sure.
AGENT: Yeah yeah I mean look and I look I know it sucks that you do have to pay
that much up front right?
CUSTOMER: Yeah it's a lot of money that I don't have.
AGENT: Yeah no I know and I'm
completely aware of that like it's not it's not ideal right like I get that but
it is the best psych institution in Australia and it is a way into that fourth year
and you can do it a hundred percent online as well.
not_enrolled.justification: The agent acexpertises the customer's concern over the significant upfront payment required for the first two products and informs them that the remaining products are covered under fee help, thus directly addressing affordability concerns. By recognizing the financial barrier and highlighting the value and benefits of the portfolio, including its reputation as the best psychology institution in Australia and offering the flexibility of a fully online portfolio, the agent conforms to the Fee Affordability Concern Resolution criteria.

not_enrolled.evidence: CUSTOMER: I just can't afford the $10,000 upfront, so... AGENT: false, no, no. Look, that's OK. That's absolutely fine. I'll put you through to our customer advisers now to get that all sorted, OK?
not_enrolled.justification: The customer explicitly mentions an affordability concern regarding the $10,000 upfront cost. While the agent acexpertises the concern, there is no attempt to explore financial barriers or offer payment solutions, such as FEE-HELP, as recommended by the taxonomy. Instead, the agent proceeds to transfer the call, focusing more on processing the un-conversion rather than resolution of the fee affordability concern.

AGENT: Okay, sure thing.
AGENT: Not a problem.

enrolled_not_retained.evidence:

The agent acexpertises the concern and provides information about bonus return options available, addressing the fee affordability concern without making unverified claims, which aligns with the 'Fee Affordability Concern Resolution' category.

enrolled_retained.evidence:
CUSTOMER: And the cost is around $60,000? That's a lot of money. I'm not sure if I can afford that.
AGENT: I understand your concern about the cost - it is a significant investment. May I ask what specific aspects of the cost are most concerning to you? Is it the total amount, or more about the timing of payments?

enrolled_retained.evidence: AGENT: Now the cost per product is $4,837.50. These products cannot be put on to fee help, so you'll need to pay the first product in the first week of starting the subject. Now once you finalize these first two subjects, if you're successful in moving into the Grad Diplostack Advanced, the rest of the investment product can go on to fee help.
enrolled_retained.justification: The agent directly addresses the concern of upfront payment for the investment product cost and offers a resolution by explaining the potential access to fee help for subsequent products, effectively addressing fee affordability concerns.

not_enrolled.evidence:
AGENT: If you want January I'd decide pretty quickly.
CUSTOMER: Okay, I'll think about it tonight and I'll get back to you.
AGENT: Yeah, yeah, no that's absolutely fine, take your time, that's okay, don't worry.
not_enrolled.justification: The agent successfully triggers immediate action by emphasizing the urgency of deciding quickly if the customer wants to investl in January. Despite reassuring the customer, this creates a sense of urgency that encourages the customer to think about the decision promptly and respond soon after the call.

not_enrolled.evidence: AGENT: Now, would you like me to assess your performance ratings for you so we can let you know what you're sitting on so you can make a decision. CUSTOMER: Yeah, I mean, I don't think I get my finalized transcript until about three o'clock. AGENT: Yeah, that's fine. I'll send you an email with the handbook for just the grad dip of psych advance, so you can respond with the document once you've got it, and then we'll just calculate your performance ratings there, just to let you know what you're sitting on, so you can decide what you wish to do.
not_enrolled.justification: The agent encourages the customer to take immediate post-call action by sending the transcript for rating review as soon as they receive it. This action is an immediate step towards progressing through the conversion decision-making process.

enrolled_not_retained.evidence: AGENT: For now, if you can reply back to me with your ID, I think I should be able to investl you for the investment product directly, okay, until we wait for that official financial transcript. I mean, basically, obviously, they're going to send it off to you by Friday if you request them today.
enrolled_not_retained.justification: The agent encourages immediate action by asking the customer to send their ID immediately after the call, facilitating conversion without waiting for the official transcript. This specific request triggers the conversion process immediately and is planned before the Friday deadline to mitigate any delays.

enrolled_not_retained.evidence: AGENT: Are you happy to do that today? CUSTOMER: Yes I can. AGENT: Okay, excellent. Do you have access to your emails right now? CUSTOMER: Right now I'm in our office so I can do it once we hang up the call. AGENT: So your place is not secure until you accept the customer declaration, and places do fill up very quickly, so it's very important that you, once you finish this call, go into your emails and click accept on the customer declaration.
enrolled_not_retained.justification: The agent successfully encourages the customer to initiate immediate post-call actions by securing a commitment to check their email and finalize the necessary conversion steps. This is further reinforced by creating urgency about the customer's place not being secure until the declaration is accepted.

enrolled_retained.evidence:
AGENT: Do you have access to your emails at the moment?
CUSTOMER: I do, I do.
AGENT: Perfect, so we do just need this one to be accepted over the phone so I can confirm your investment has gone through successfully.
enrolled_retained.justification: The agent effectively encourages immediate action by asking the customer to access their email to confirm conversion during the call itself, demonstrating immediate action triggering.

enrolled_retained.evidence: AGENT: We can do it now. It'll take about five minutes. So what we'll do is really straightforward. We'll start off by confirming your details and then while we're on the phone, I will also email you or text you an investment declaration form, which you just need to press accept while you're on the phone.
enrolled_retained.justification: The agent effectively triggers immediate action by initiating the conversion process during the call, guiding the customer to confirm their details and accept the conversion declaration form. This demonstrates a successful encouragement of specific post-call actions that initiate the conversion process.
